<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910702-0063</DOCNO><DOCID>910702-0063.</DOCID><HL>   Letters to the Editor:   Her Own Monster</HL><DATE>07/02/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A13</SO><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   I read with sardonic amusement John Fund's May 31editorial-page article on the troubles of Susan Alter, the&quot;liberal's liberal.&quot; She probably helped create the&quot;politically correct&quot; Frankenstein's monster that is nowdoing her in. Liberals often assume that the abstractconcepts of do-goodism are on the agenda of those theybelieve they are helping -- unaware that the real agenda isusually the assumption and control of power. And if the Billof Rights and our political mores go down the tubes as aconsequence, so be it. After all, these are Anglo-Saxon,Eurocentric constructs.   I would laugh uproariously at her plight if I didn't hearthe shuffling steps of this monster getting closer.</LP><TEXT>   Harold Glaser   Berkeley, Calif.</TEXT></DOC>